WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Good to have Mike visiting with us this evening

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.480
and found us online and thankful that he's here tonight.

00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:07.739
Good to have Arthur back with us as well.

00:00:07.739 --> 00:00:09.819
And he'd visited a number of Sundays ago

00:00:09.819 --> 00:00:11.979
and good to have him here this evening.

00:00:11.979 --> 00:00:12.979
If you have your Bible with you,

00:00:12.979 --> 00:00:15.479
Genesis chapter number one this evening,

00:00:15.479 --> 00:00:17.219
Genesis chapter number one.

00:00:17.219 --> 00:00:19.760
And last week we started a new series here

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:22.959
on Wednesday evenings dealing with the names of God.

00:00:22.959 --> 00:00:25.799
And we had studied through Psalm 11

00:00:25.799 --> 00:00:28.139
and then the Lord put I my trust.

00:00:28.239 --> 00:00:31.680
And now we're getting into the names of God.

00:00:31.680 --> 00:00:35.220
Last week specifically, we went through Psalm 91

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:37.880
and there's a phrase in that Psalm.

00:00:37.880 --> 00:00:40.560
And it says this in verse number 14,

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:43.380
because he hath known my name.

00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:45.020
And we dealt with that last week

00:00:45.020 --> 00:00:48.959
and how important it is that we know the names of God.

00:00:48.959 --> 00:00:52.500
And we understand that as we studied last week

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:55.939
and dealt with the importance of knowing God's name

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:59.299
and then the impact of knowing God's names.

00:00:59.299 --> 00:01:01.680
And he has given to us in his word,

00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:05.080
he's revealed various aspects of his nature

00:01:05.080 --> 00:01:08.540
and attributes to us through his names.

00:01:08.540 --> 00:01:11.019
We're gonna start in Genesis chapter number one.

00:01:11.019 --> 00:01:13.120
Although it's important for me to know

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.379
even at the onset this evening,

00:01:15.379 --> 00:01:17.860
that this is not the first name

00:01:17.860 --> 00:01:20.519
that God revealed to mankind,

00:01:20.519 --> 00:01:23.099
because the first name that are revealed to mankind

00:01:23.099 --> 00:01:26.099
was when he was speaking with Abraham.

00:01:26.099 --> 00:01:28.260
And he was actually Abram at the time,

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:30.660
his name had not yet been changed.

00:01:30.660 --> 00:01:33.099
And actually we find that God recorded

00:01:33.099 --> 00:01:35.839
and gave to Abram a number of names

00:01:35.839 --> 00:01:40.440
referring to himself that he reveals to Abram.

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:43.779
But of course, we have the whole canon of scripture.

00:01:43.779 --> 00:01:45.239
We have the Bible,

00:01:45.239 --> 00:01:48.879
the Pentateuch was written humanly speaking by Moses.

00:01:48.879 --> 00:01:51.260
And Moses gives us that record of course,

00:01:51.279 --> 00:01:54.379
way after the life of Abram, Abraham.

00:01:54.379 --> 00:01:56.720
And so the very first name that we have

00:01:56.720 --> 00:02:00.099
in the pages of scripture is found

00:02:00.099 --> 00:02:02.319
in Genesis chapter number one.

00:02:02.319 --> 00:02:05.559
And it's the Hebrew name Elohim.

00:02:05.559 --> 00:02:06.639
Elohim.

00:02:06.639 --> 00:02:09.100
And the Hebrew word is translated God,

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:13.600
it's used of the one true God over 2,300 times

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:15.279
in the Old Testament.

00:02:15.279 --> 00:02:18.479
And so really it's the most common name of God

00:02:18.479 --> 00:02:21.080
throughout the Old Testament is Elohim.

00:02:21.899 --> 00:02:24.000
And we find that there are about 260 references

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.639
or times in which the Hebrew word Elohim is used.

00:02:27.639 --> 00:02:31.820
And it's not referring to the one true God,

00:02:31.820 --> 00:02:34.039
it's used in a generic sense.

00:02:34.039 --> 00:02:35.619
And it's important for us to understand,

00:02:35.619 --> 00:02:37.160
we're not gonna look at all that this evening,

00:02:37.160 --> 00:02:40.460
but the context always makes it clear

00:02:40.460 --> 00:02:42.759
whether it's using the term generically

00:02:42.759 --> 00:02:45.899
or if it's speaking about the one true God.

00:02:45.899 --> 00:02:47.899
And we find that it's important

00:02:47.899 --> 00:02:50.960
as we've made known many times over the years

00:02:51.779 --> 00:02:53.580
of the context that God gives us.

00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:56.479
But notice in Genesis one, in verse number one,

00:02:56.479 --> 00:03:00.199
notice the Bible says, in the beginning, God.

00:03:00.199 --> 00:03:03.020
That's the word Elohim, the name of God

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:06.100
that is given to us in Genesis chapter number one

00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:07.440
is Elohim.

00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:08.559
And it says in the beginning,

00:03:08.559 --> 00:03:13.000
God created the heaven and the earth.

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.940
The name Elohim means strong one.

00:03:16.800 --> 00:03:18.779
That's literally what it means,

00:03:18.779 --> 00:03:20.600
the strong one, the mighty one.

00:03:21.220 --> 00:03:22.720
Some have used that as well.

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:26.199
But we find that the name of God, Elohim,

00:03:26.199 --> 00:03:30.440
is used 32 times in Genesis chapter number one.

00:03:31.539 --> 00:03:32.600
Now think about that.

00:03:32.600 --> 00:03:35.539
Genesis chapter number one has 31 verses.

00:03:35.539 --> 00:03:40.539
And the name Elohim for God is used 32 times in 31 verses.

00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:44.279
And so what do we learn about that?

00:03:44.279 --> 00:03:47.820
We notice as we begin to study this first name of God

00:03:47.820 --> 00:03:50.559
that is given to us in the pages of scripture,

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:54.960
that the name Elohim has an obvious connection

00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:57.800
to God as creator.

00:03:57.800 --> 00:04:00.279
We find that as we begin to think about the fact

00:04:00.279 --> 00:04:01.960
that he is the strong one

00:04:01.960 --> 00:04:04.279
and that there's this obvious connection

00:04:04.279 --> 00:04:07.039
with regard to God being the creator,

00:04:07.039 --> 00:04:10.160
we find that he is the creator and he is the ruler.

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:13.880
He has power and he has authority.

00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:15.600
We find that in Jeremiah,

00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:17.760
if you wanna hold your place there in Genesis

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:22.079
and flip over quickly to Jeremiah chapter 51,

00:04:22.079 --> 00:04:24.799
the word Elohim is not specifically used

00:04:24.799 --> 00:04:26.200
here in Jeremiah 51,

00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:27.640
but it's a great verse of scripture

00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:31.000
to just remind us of the power that God has

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.239
that was displayed through creation.

00:04:34.239 --> 00:04:38.320
And we find here in Jeremiah 51 in verse number 15,

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:41.760
he hath made the earth by his power.

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:45.679
He hath established the world by his wisdom

00:04:45.679 --> 00:04:50.640
and hath stretched out the heaven by his understanding.

00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:53.559
So we find this evening that as we consider

00:04:53.559 --> 00:04:56.359
that creation reveals the power of God,

00:04:56.359 --> 00:05:00.260
yes, there are other names that God uses of himself

00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:03.420
that would describe God's strength and God's power,

00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:05.480
but it's this name Elohim

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:10.480
that has this direct connection with regard to creation.

00:05:10.899 --> 00:05:12.600
We understand that God created,

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:15.160
we read it in Genesis one in verse number one,

00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:18.679
he created everything out of nothing.

00:05:18.679 --> 00:05:21.619
He spoke it all into existence.

00:05:21.619 --> 00:05:23.279
Now you understand this evening

00:05:23.279 --> 00:05:27.320
that this fundamental truth of Genesis chapter number one,

00:05:27.320 --> 00:05:30.320
that many of us on a Wednesday evening prayer meeting say,

00:05:30.320 --> 00:05:32.600
yes, we believe God is the creator.

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:35.600
I want you to understand with great clarity this evening

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:38.799
that this fundamental truth is under great attack

00:05:38.799 --> 00:05:43.160
in our society today and it has been for generations.

00:05:43.160 --> 00:05:46.320
We find that this truth of God being the creator

00:05:46.320 --> 00:05:48.200
is constantly being attacked.

00:05:48.200 --> 00:05:51.980
They seek to undermine the opening pages of scripture

00:05:51.980 --> 00:05:54.920
and they try to eliminate, if you will,

00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:58.640
the really first 11 chapters of the book of Genesis,

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:01.279
but we find that the truth of creation

00:06:01.279 --> 00:06:05.040
is not isolated to Genesis chapter number one.

00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:07.040
The truth of creation can be found

00:06:07.040 --> 00:06:09.059
throughout the whole of scripture.

00:06:09.059 --> 00:06:11.959
We find many of God's people, God's servants

00:06:11.959 --> 00:06:16.959
that will refer to and speak of God being the creator.

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:20.279
And what a blessing that we have so much scripture

00:06:20.279 --> 00:06:23.179
that gives us the truth and the reality

00:06:23.179 --> 00:06:25.799
that our God is the creator.

00:06:25.799 --> 00:06:27.640
Romans one gives us great insight

00:06:27.640 --> 00:06:31.720
as to why there's such an attack on the subject of creation

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:35.619
and why there are so many that have fought so vehemently

00:06:35.619 --> 00:06:40.339
to deny the existence of God and to deny the creation

00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:44.299
is because if they can remove God as creator,

00:06:44.299 --> 00:06:48.739
then they no longer are subject to God.

00:06:48.739 --> 00:06:51.380
And really that's ultimately what man wants to do

00:06:51.380 --> 00:06:53.500
in their unregenerate state.

00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:56.059
And we find that to be the case

00:06:56.059 --> 00:06:59.299
so prevalent in our school systems today.

00:06:59.299 --> 00:07:01.299
I mean, children that are going through

00:07:01.299 --> 00:07:04.179
the public school system today,

00:07:04.179 --> 00:07:06.619
they are constantly, the university system,

00:07:06.619 --> 00:07:09.299
they're constantly being bombarded

00:07:09.299 --> 00:07:13.480
with this Darwinian evolution being taught theory

00:07:13.480 --> 00:07:16.500
as if it is law and fact.

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:18.459
And they're undermining the truth of scripture,

00:07:18.459 --> 00:07:22.299
but the reality is God says in our opening passage

00:07:22.299 --> 00:07:24.100
of scripture in Genesis chapter one,

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:27.119
he gives to us a record of creation

00:07:27.119 --> 00:07:31.100
and we read these words, God said, and it was so.

00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:32.820
And I love that phrase.

00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:35.220
Of course, it's separated by whatever it was

00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:37.339
that God said, and it was so.

00:07:37.339 --> 00:07:39.420
Let's just read a few verses of scripture here

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:41.179
in Genesis chapter number one

00:07:41.179 --> 00:07:45.540
and see the references that God gives us with this name,

00:07:45.540 --> 00:07:48.380
this first name that he gives us of Elohim.

00:07:48.380 --> 00:07:52.739
In the beginning, God created the heaven and the earth

00:07:52.739 --> 00:07:54.799
and the earth was without form and void

00:07:54.799 --> 00:07:57.220
and darkness was upon the face of the deep

00:07:57.220 --> 00:08:00.059
and the spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters

00:08:01.100 --> 00:08:06.100
and God, Elohim, and God said, let there be light

00:08:06.619 --> 00:08:08.299
and there was light.

00:08:08.299 --> 00:08:10.820
I hope that the truth of Genesis 1, 3

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:12.779
never grows old to you.

00:08:12.779 --> 00:08:16.739
I hope that the power and the wisdom of Genesis 1

00:08:16.739 --> 00:08:20.899
in verse number three is impactful in your life today

00:08:20.899 --> 00:08:23.299
as much as it was the very first time

00:08:23.299 --> 00:08:25.380
you ever read that verse of scripture

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:30.040
that God said, let there be light and there was light.

00:08:30.040 --> 00:08:32.260
You understand this evening that no one else

00:08:32.260 --> 00:08:33.739
could ever make that claim.

00:08:33.739 --> 00:08:36.539
No one else could ever do that.

00:08:36.539 --> 00:08:39.700
But God, the strong one, the mighty one, Elohim,

00:08:39.700 --> 00:08:42.580
he said, let there be light and there was light.

00:08:42.580 --> 00:08:45.739
It continues in God saw the light that it was good

00:08:45.739 --> 00:08:48.080
and God divided the light from the darkness

00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:51.219
and God called the light day and the darkness he called night

00:08:51.219 --> 00:08:53.960
and the evening and the morning were the first day

00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:55.859
and God said, let there be a firmament

00:08:55.859 --> 00:08:57.039
in the midst of the waters

00:08:57.039 --> 00:09:00.140
and let it divide the waters from the waters

00:09:00.140 --> 00:09:02.979
and God made the firmament and divided the waters

00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:05.020
which were under the firmament from the waters

00:09:05.020 --> 00:09:08.419
which were above the firmament and it was so

00:09:08.419 --> 00:09:10.739
and God called the firmament heaven

00:09:10.739 --> 00:09:13.780
and the evening and the morning were the second day

00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:16.140
and God said, we see again there in verse nine,

00:09:16.140 --> 00:09:19.200
let the waters under the heaven be gathered together

00:09:19.200 --> 00:09:24.200
unto one place and let the dry land appear and it was so.

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:29.219
Verse number 10, and God called the dry land earth

00:09:29.219 --> 00:09:31.659
and the gathering together of the waters called he seas

00:09:31.659 --> 00:09:34.539
and God saw that it was good

00:09:34.539 --> 00:09:37.460
and God said, let the earth bring forth grass,

00:09:37.460 --> 00:09:40.739
the herb yielding seed and the fruit tree yielding fruit

00:09:40.739 --> 00:09:45.460
after his kind whose seed is in itself upon the earth

00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:46.820
and it was so.

00:09:46.820 --> 00:09:49.419
The earth brought forth grass and herb yielding seed

00:09:49.419 --> 00:09:51.820
after his kind and the tree yielding fruit

00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:54.460
whose seed was in itself after his kind

00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:56.859
and God saw that it was good

00:09:56.859 --> 00:09:58.799
and the evening and the morning were the third day

00:09:58.799 --> 00:09:59.840
and God said.

00:09:59.840 --> 00:10:02.060
Let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:03.720
to divide the day from the night.

00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:06.300
Let them be for signs and for seasons

00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:07.680
and for days and years.

00:10:07.680 --> 00:10:10.640
And let them be for lights in the firmament of the heaven

00:10:10.640 --> 00:10:11.920
to give light upon the earth.

00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:13.000
And it was so.

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:14.680
And God made two great lights,

00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:16.280
the greater light to rule the day

00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:19.040
and the lesser light to rule the night.

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:20.640
He made the stars also.

00:10:21.640 --> 00:10:24.920
I know you've heard me say it before from verse number 16,

00:10:24.920 --> 00:10:28.480
how impactful and amazing those five words

00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:30.680
that end verse 16 are.

00:10:30.680 --> 00:10:33.080
He made the stars also.

00:10:33.080 --> 00:10:35.080
You can't number the stars.

00:10:35.080 --> 00:10:37.600
You look up, I understand we live close to the city.

00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:39.800
You can't see hardly as many stars here

00:10:39.800 --> 00:10:42.480
as you can in some places of the country.

00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:46.680
And you look up and you're just absolutely amazed.

00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:48.680
And it says that he made the stars also.

00:10:48.680 --> 00:10:51.440
Verse 17, and God set them in the firmament of the heaven

00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:52.760
to give light upon the earth

00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:55.280
and to rule over the day and over the night

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:56.980
and to divide the light from the darkness.

00:10:56.980 --> 00:10:59.540
And God saw that it was good.

00:10:59.540 --> 00:11:02.620
